Hlaudi Motsoeneng faced charges of bringing the SABC into disrepute and causing irreparable damage. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) will announce the outcome of Hlaudi Motsoeneng's disciplinary hearing at a press conference on Monday afternoon.The former chief operating officer appeared before the disciplinary committee on Friday on charges of contravening the terms of his suspension after holding a briefing in April during which he attacked the broadcaster's interim board and Parliament's inquiry into the corporation.Interim board chairperson of the SABC Khanyisile Kweyama is expected to make the announcement.It's understood the board has met to discuss the report that was handed in early on Monday morning.Motsoeneng faced charges of bringing the SABC into disrepute and causing irreparable damage after holding a four-hour long press briefing in April while he was on suspension.During the briefing, Motsoeneng defended his 90% local content policy and criticised the parliamentary ad-hoc committee's inquiry into the broadcaster's former board.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)